
Gasoline abuse in a 10-year-old child with mental retardation: A case report




 
Â© the authors, publisher and licensee Libertas academica Limited. Inahalant abuse is of increasing interest in India. Te age of onset is typically during adolescence. Gasoline inhalant use is rarely reported in adolescents with intellectual deficit. We report a case of petrol dependence in a 10-year-old child with mental retardation. Possible effect of petrol huffing on behavior and cognition is discussed.


